> This page documents behavior guaranteed in TealTiger v1.1.0. Final API names may evolve, but the **decision contract and semantics** are stable.

# Decision Model

## Why a Decision contract?

TealTiger returns a single, deterministic **Decision** object from policy-enforcing components so your application can handle security and cost governance outcomes **predictably**.

A Decision is designed to be:

- **Deterministic:** same inputs + same policy â†’ same output
- **Typed/structured:** you branch on `action` and `reason_codes`, not on strings in logs
- **Auditable:** the same decision data can be emitted to `AuditEvent`
- **Composable:** engine/guard/circuit all return the same structure

<Callout type="info">
Think of a Decision as a **policy result** plus **how your app should react** (block, allow, redact, transform, require approval, degrade).
</Callout>

---

## Decision in one picture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  A[RequestContext] --> B[Policy evaluation]
  B --> C{Decision.action}
  C -->|ALLOW| D[Proceed]
  C -->|DENY| E[Block + raise PolicyViolationError (ENFORCE)]
  C -->|REQUIRE_APPROVAL| F[Human approval flow]
  C -->|REDACT| G[Redact content + proceed]
  C -->|TRANSFORM| H[Transform content + proceed]
  C -->|DEGRADE| I[Fallback model / reduced capability]
  B --> J[Emit AuditEvent (redaction-safe)]
